      "message": "I\u0027m not 100% sure how we should handle this. The scratch block is re-initialized when it gets moved back to a new block, so that goes through the ctor and becomes poisoned. But it\u0027s probably a good idea to poison it here, so that any accesses to it while it\u0027s \"scratch\" are caught.\n\nThen since the head block is also supposed to be poisoned in the condition up above, maybe we just have the first step of releaseBlock() be to poison the whole range. If we end up deleting the block, its destructor will unpoison it before it\u0027s freed and that\u0027s correct. If it\u0027s not deleted, we\u0027ve made sure it\u0027s poisoned while we hold on to it for later reuse.",
